## The Outside Inn — Its Role in the Brand

**The Outside Inn is the place between places.**

Right now, it is three things: the name of E.I. Werner's official Discord, the name of the radio broadcast (Outside Inn Radio — original music by Carson Thatcher, pixel art and animation by Marwan Hasnaoui, a character named Holdt who writes alongside listeners), and a concept that lives in the brand's DNA without a rigid definition yet. The honest truth is that its full role is still being figured out. We're making this up as we go along, and that's fine.

**What we know:** The Outside Inn handles are secured across platforms. This gives the brand a secondary channel for clips, going live off-schedule, or eventually launching the 24/7 radio under its own roof. Whether it becomes a sub-brand, a content channel, an ambient art project, or something else — that will reveal itself through use. Don't over-define it prematurely.

**The conceptual territory:**

Inside · Outside · Outside Inn · Home · Destination · Inn · Welcome · Unwelcome · Invitation · Locked · Unlocked · Key · Day · Night · Dusk · Night · Day · Dawn

> **"Step inn anytime and stay."**

**The 70:07 Bookend (Mar 3):** The Outside Inn Radio bookends every live stream with a 70-minute, 7-second warmup and cooldown — Holdt animation + Carson's music + countdown timer + patron roll, all running locally in OBS. This replaced the original 24/7 radio concept. The radio proved itself technically (11h39m run, zero drops on day one), but the operational overhead of managing a VPS stream alongside live broadcasts — plus a single 80-second animation loop over 1h40m of music — doesn't justify 24/7 yet. The 70:07 bookend delivers the Outside Inn atmosphere around every stream without the complexity. The 24/7 radio becomes a future unlock when two conditions are met: headless OBS on the VPS (enabling dynamic overlays like "next stream" notices and patron rolls on the ambient broadcast) and a deeper content catalog. Both deferred to ~April 2026. The VPS infrastructure stays available.

**Discord:** The community Discord is called The Outside Inn. The open Discord is the lobby. Tier-gated channels unlock for Scriveners and Keepers via Fourthwall integration. The gated channels are the real room.

**Entity note:** Outside Inn Studios, LLC is the legal entity that operates everything — the brand, the streams, the merch, the memberships. EIN 39-3932425. NY DOS ID 7690233. Formed August 20, 2025. Evan Werner, 100% member-managed. The LLC is the business. E.I. Werner is the voice.

