## ONCE — The Mythology

> **Logline:** Seven original myths braid astrophysics, philosophy, and religion into a single, foundational hymn—tracing humanity's emergence from before the Beginning.

> **Introduction:** The best fantasy isn't an escape. It's a destination—somewhere you travel to and then return from carrying a matryoshka doll that takes a lifetime to unpack. ONCE is the mythology of such a destination. Not a fantasy world, but the Big Bang and Bible for those who live there. A compendium of seven hymns that hum with the familiar gravity of Genesis and thunder of Olympus. But they strike a different chord—a dire warning that binds their civilization in a singular purpose. The sun will die. And only we can save it.

**What it is:** Seven original creation myths forming the complete cosmology of a fantasy world. A moral philosophy built from scratch, with answers to the questions every civilization must answer. This is the first product the brand will deliver to the world — the foundational creative work that everything else will be built on.

**Why it matters beyond the brand:** ONCE is not worldbuilding notes dressed up as content. It braids astrophysics, philosophy, and religion into something that functions the way Genesis or the Greek myths function — as a foundational text that shapes how an entire civilization understands itself. The core dramatic engine is a warning: the sun will die, and only we can save it. That premise binds the mythology together and gives every hymn stakes that feel both cosmic and immediate.

**What this does for the brand statement:** "Writing, fantasy, and games are not escapes. They are destinations." The ONCE introduction IS the brand statement made specific. The mythology is literally a destination — not a fantasy world to escape into, but a place you travel to and return from carrying something. The matryoshka doll image — something that takes a lifetime to unpack — is the promise the brand makes to its audience. This is not disposable content. This is work that rewards return visits.

**Current status (Mar 3, 2026):** 6 milestones complete (see table below), including 6 of 7 outlines. CHOSEN outline due tomorrow (Mar 4). KEEPER & Complete outlines due Mar 11. The mythology is being written in the Analog workshop under Ravi Gupta, with documented deadlines and accountability both in class and on stream. First live writing stream is tomorrow at 7:07 AM — the first time the ONCE writing process will be visible to an audience in real time.

**Target completion:** September 9, 2026 — ONCE Complete.

**Release format:** TBD. The priority right now is writing purity — finishing the mythology to the standard it deserves. Packaging decisions (art book, serialized release, standalone publication, read-aloud on stream, or something else) will be made once the writing is further along. The bible should not lock in a format prematurely.

### The Seven Hymns

ONCE is both the name of the compendium and the name of the first hymn. The mythology is called ONCE. The first myth within it is also called ONCE — the origin story that gives the whole work its name. Seven hymns total. Each progresses through a defined stage system:

| Stage | What It Means |
|---|---|
| Outline | Structural blueprint — what happens, how it connects |
| Reader | Draft readable by someone generous — the story works on the page |
| Hater | Draft that survives hostile scrutiny — airtight, no excuses |
| Complete | Final — the hymn is done |

### The Hymns (in writing order)

1. **ONCE** — The origin. The hymn that names the mythology.
2. **MOTHER**
3. **BROTHER**
4. **WAR**
5. **GATE**
6. **CHOSEN**
7. **KEEPER** — Shares a name with the retired novel. The connection is intentional and runs deep.

**ONCE Complete** is the final milestone — the mythology unified, all seven hymns done.

