## Content Strategy

### The Cadence

**3 sessions per week: writing → gaming in each session.**

Each stream opens with writing — the ONCE mythology, live in Notion, with a defined goal for the session. Then transitions into gaming with community as the decompression and debrief. Writing is the main event. Gaming is the exhale. This structure fits the Athens timezone naturally (morning writing intensity, afternoon/evening gaming and chill) and eliminates the old tension of a standalone gaming stream that might drain more than it gives.

The 70:07 Outside Inn warmup opens every stream. The 70:07 cooldown closes it.

This replaces the previous plan of 3 writing streams + 1 dedicated gaming stream per week. The integrated format keeps gaming present as community glue without requiring a separate content commitment.

### Monthly public update videos — ungated.

Straight look at how the month went, what moved, what didn't. These are the pieces most likely to bring new people in via recommendation. They serve as rooting interest recruitment.

### The 75/20/5 Content Mix

**75% — Deep content.** ONCE mythology breakdowns, worldbuilding process, writing philosophy, the rejection ledger lived out loud, craft notes. This builds trust with the audience that will eventually buy the books and the mythology.

**20% — Niche-wide content.** Broadly relevant to fantasy lovers, gamers, and writers — but still within Evan's world. What makes great fantasy. How gaming builds community. What the writing life actually looks like. Reaches new people who are adjacent to the offer.

**5% — Personal content (sprinkled in, not dedicated videos).** Gaming references, music taste, the nerdy obsessions, the human layer. Not standalone pieces — elements woven through the 75% and 20%. What makes the brand impossible to copy. *(Note: The human layer inventory needs to be completed — see [Open Questions](#open-questions--gaps).)*

### The Content Success Formula

**Painful Problem + Unique Solution × Contextual Credibility × Proven Wrapper = Content That Converts**

Contextual credibility is more powerful than general credibility. "I've been writing fantasy for 18 years" is general. "I built a complete cosmological moral philosophy from scratch across seven creation myths and I'm still refining it" is contextual. Lead with the specific.

### Ideation Engine

Every painful problem from The Three Audiences section is a stream, a video, a conversation, a piece of content. There are 16 problems listed across the three audiences (once validated — see note above). Cross-reference them with the credibility bank and the contrarian positions — every intersection is a new angle.

### Content Scaling Frameworks (from workshop)

**The Accordion Method** — Expand (high volume, data collection) → Contract (focus effort on what the data says works) → Expand again (audience fatigues, try new things). This cycle never ends.

**70/20/10 Framework:** 70% content proven to work (reliability). 20% iterations of the 70% (optimization). 10% big swings and experiments (innovation — finding the NEXT thing before audience fatigue hits). The 10% is the most important and most neglected.

**Current phase:** Pre-data. Everything is an experiment. The Accordion is in its first Expand phase. Track what works, what energizes Evan, and what the audience responds to. Contract once there's enough data to know what's working. The first stream just happened — the data era has begun.

### Trust Over Virality

For high-ticket or niche audiences, optimizing for virality typically produces: views up, followers up, content gets wider and more diluted, original audience tunes out, sales go down.

Trust is the goal. The trust-building content pattern: identify the painful problem → share the unique solution → set clear expectations → make it actionable → repeat consistently. Months of this pattern = strong belief that the brand delivers value. When a paid offer appears, the mental leap is small.

### Cold Audience Principle

Every piece of content must work for someone who has zero clue who E.I. Werner is. No inside jokes, no unexplained references, no assumed knowledge of backstory. This is especially critical during the launch phase when every viewer is cold.

