## Platform Strategy

### Eye of Sauron — YouTube First

YouTube is the primary platform. It gets the pillar content: the long-form writing/gaming streams, the monthly update videos, the Outside Inn 70:07 bookends. All energy, all innovation, all creative risk goes here first.

Twitch is secondary — simulcast from OBS, live community interaction, gaming culture home. No rebuild required. It receives the stream, not the innovation.

TikTok, Instagram, YouTube Shorts receive repurposed clips only. No original creation for these platforms in year one. One editor takes raw stream footage and outputs VODs plus clips — one person, one workflow, three outputs.

**This phase ends when YouTube feels dialed in.** Then the Eye rotates to short-form with real intention. Not before.

**First stream status (Mar 3, 2026):** Broadcast Alpha is live. First stream happened today. 8 peak viewers — told almost nobody. The Holdt radio ran for 11 hours, 39 minutes, 11 seconds without a single drop before Evan took it down to go live himself. YouTube's 24-hour countdown for new streamers (triggered Feb 26) cleared, and the stream went out. No overlay, no polish. Just showed up. The tech worked. The awkwardness was real. It only goes up from here.

