## The First Three Videos

### Video 1 — Channel Introduction

**What it is:** The 18-year story made useful to the viewer. Not a biography. Not a brag reel. The story as a shortcut for them.

**The script draft opens:** "I'm E.I. Werner and I've been an aspiring fantasy author for 18 years. I've written a lot and taken real shots but don't have much to show for it."

Rejection quotes appear on screen. Not as wounds. As evidence of real swings.

The pivotal moments: deciding at 15. The Keeper going out to every major publisher. The retirement letter. The ONCE mythology beginning. Each moment carries a lesson that is immediately useful to the viewer.

Closes with the brand statement and the sign-off. "While you're here, you're already there."

**The test:** Would you be comfortable sending this to people whose opinion you actually care about? Yes. That is the bar.

### Video 2 — What Is ONCE

**What it is:** An introduction to the mythology — what Evan is actually writing and why it matters.

Opens with: "Writing, fantasy, and games are not escapes. They are destinations." Everything that follows is the argument for that claim, made concrete through the ONCE project.

Explains what it means to build a moral philosophy from scratch across seven creation myths. Walks through what fantasy actually does that realism cannot. Introduces the world, the premise (the sun will die, and only we can save it), and the scale of ambition. Gives the viewer a reason to care about the writing before the book exists.

### Video 3 — First Month Review

**What it is:** Straight look at how the first month of streaming went. What moved, what didn't, what surprised him. Honest, ungated, useful.

This is the template for monthly update videos going forward. It serves as rooting interest recruitment — a new viewer can watch this and immediately understand the stakes, the progress, and the personality.

### Future Video Ideas (Parking Lot)

- The Positioning Deep Dive: Why Fantasy Actually Matters (25+ min, the full argument for the brand statement)
- Making the Machinima: behind-the-scenes of building WoW machinima Episode 1 — learning a new medium in public
- The Rejection Ledger: the full story told through the actual quotes

