## Technology & Operational Advantage

Most creator brands at this stage hire contractors or agencies for ecommerce setup, streaming infrastructure, payment integration, analytics, and tooling. Outside Inn doesn't need to. Evan's background eliminates the need for outside technical help on nearly everything the brand touches in year one and beyond.

**What this means practically:**

**Ecommerce & Payments:** Evan integrated 8+ payment types onto a single platform at SKIMS, architected order management across OMS/ERP/WMS, and built the middleware connecting all of it. Setting up Fourthwall, managing product feeds, pricing logic, and payment flows is execution, not learning. If the brand outgrows Fourthwall, he knows exactly when and how to migrate — he's made build-vs-buy decisions at 600k+ order-day scale.

**Streaming & Infrastructure:** The entire OBS/Restream stack, dual-WAN failover, battery backup architecture, and scene automation were designed and configured by Evan. No streaming consultant. No IT hire. The 99.9% uptime target is informed by maintaining 99.6% order flow uptime during peak traffic events at SKIMS. Day one validated the core infrastructure: 11h39m radio broadcast without a drop, successful live stream, all hardware performing.

**Day-One Tech Wins (Mar 3):** In the 48 hours before Broadcast Alpha, Evan built the animation pipeline from scratch — 480 raw PNGs from Marwan → DaVinci Resolve → FFmpeg → final HoldtLoop.mp4 deployed to VPS. Built the countdown timer (countdown_alagard.html) and patron roll typewriter (patron_roll_typewriter.html) as local OBS browser sources in Alagard pixel font. Learned HTML overlay development through Claude pair-programming and now understands it well enough to iterate independently. Solved four distinct streaming issues on launch day (YouTube stream key reset, Restream channel toggle, FFmpeg suspension, YouTube Studio dashboard confusion — all documented in the OIS Hardware & Software Master). This is the technical advantage in action: problems that would have required a consultant got solved in real time.

**Data & Analytics:** Built Watchtower (real-time financial dashboard for SKIMS CFO), Apollo (CX platform replacing Shopify admin for 108/117 agents, 94% error reduction), and Lighthouse (retail operations visibility). Can build his own dashboards and analytics for OIS revenue, merch performance, and stream metrics without third-party tools or hires.

**AI Tooling:** Led Netomi AI chatbot implementation at SKIMS (16% ticket reduction). Built a secure API knowledge base integrated with GitHub Copilot (18% faster engineering velocity). Uses Claude and other AI tools as production infrastructure for brand operations, content strategy, and document management — not as novelty. The animation pipeline and HTML overlays built pre-launch were Claude pair-programming outputs.

**Agile & Scaling:** Introduced Scrum to SKIMS from scratch, scaled the tech team from ~5 to 40+, rebuilt company-wide Jira for 116 weekly users, consolidated three Notion workspaces into one. When OIS needs to bring on team members, the project management and collaboration infrastructure already exists in Evan's muscle memory.

**What this saves:** Conservative estimate — $2,000–$5,000/month in contractor costs that a non-technical founder at this stage would need for ecommerce setup, streaming infrastructure, integrations, and basic analytics. That's runway.

**Expert Network Validation:** Evan is an active expert on GLG, AlphaSights, and Guidepoint at $399/hour. Clients pay for his ecommerce infrastructure knowledge. The same expertise that commands consulting fees is deployed full-time on Outside Inn at no incremental cost.

