### Merch Samples — First Impressions (Mar 3)

Evan received physical merch samples on Broadcast Alpha day: a desk mat and a 10×10 framed goose print.

**Desk mat:** High quality print, but the aspect ratio is too square. Needs the wider Fourthwall desk mat format. New samples to be ordered for both the Outside Inn collection (Marwan's art) and the illustration collection (Luiz's art) in the correct wider dimensions.

**10×10 Framed Print:** The image looks blown up and lower quality than expected. The source illustration was not painted at high enough resolution for crisp printing at this size. Luiz now knows the required specs — future paintings will be done at higher resolution. The existing products may need to be re-evaluated or the art re-exported at better quality where possible.

**Action items:** Order new desk mat samples in wider format. Revisit 10×10 print source resolution with Luiz. Communicate clearly on resolution specs for all future artwork commissions — this was a gap in the original brief.

### Fourthwall Store Collections (Launch)

All collections sourced from a single Luiz illustration — different frames and crops create distinct product lines from one piece of art.

**"There I" Collection** — Aspirational landscape frames from the full illustration. Multiple products at standard pricing.

**"There II" Collection** — Second set of aspirational frames, different crops from the same illustration.

**Goose Series** — Individual 10×10 square crops of each goose from the illustration. Clean, standalone character pieces. Goose 10×10 Unframed: $28.07. Goose 10×10 Framed: $49.07.

**Prelaunch Exclusives:** Select items from these collections will only be available during prelaunch. Once the store goes live, they are gone permanently. Scarcity is real, not manufactured.

**Merch Strategy:** Luiz's single illustration generates numerous collections and product lines. Additional collections will roll out over time from the same and future artwork. This keeps the catalog growing without requiring constant new commissions.

