| Sep 29, 2020 | Claire Stetzer (Bloomsbury) | "I struggled with the worldbuilding here." | Structure |
| Feb 16, 2021 | Tricia Nirwani (Del Rey) | "I love the idea of queering the Harry Potter mythos… this feels more suited to full-on YA." | Category |
| Apr 20, 2021 | Ali Fisher (Tor) | "I just never quite fell into the story." | Fit / Immersion |
| Jun 22, 2021 | Nancy Siscoe (Crown/PRH) | Pass. No feedback provided. | Administrative |

**Pattern:** The publisher phase surfaced the Category problem that eventually killed The Keeper: it sat between YA and Adult, and nobody knew where to shelve it. Del Rey loved the concept but called it YA. Sourcebooks said the voice was too young for YA. The book was caught in no-man's-land. Evan read this pattern, did a paid editorial assessment, sat with it, and retired the project on his own terms (May 2023). That's not failure — that's a writer reading the data and making a hard call.

