### Ledger Summary

| Category | Count |
|---|---|
| Film Passes (Marathon) | 7 |
| Agent Passes (Keeper) | 12+ |
| Publisher Passes (Keeper) | 10+ |
| Silent / No-response | Multiple |

**The through-line across the entire ledger:** The writing was almost never the problem. The rejections cluster around market positioning, category confusion, personal taste, and timing. Every campaign that generated rejections also generated real interest — Brendan Deneen signed The Keeper, producers engaged with Marathon, the CEO of Penguin Random House replied personally. The record is not a list of failures. It is proof of real swings at real targets.

